{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS 1 (A1 anti-slop/over-engineering): CLEAN — no findings.\n\nAffirmations:\n- No NIH: the plan reinstates metrics by reconstructing them from the interpreter's already-recorded per-step `duration_ms` (src/rebar/llm/workflow/interpreter.py:489-502) rather than building new instrumentation. The det/llm tier split (`_DET_STEP_IDS`/`_LLM_STEP_KINDS` in gate_dispatch.py:117-118) reuses existing step_id/kind data.\n- No config-surface proliferation: no new config keys; metrics flow through the existing `coverage` dict and existing sidecar lift (sidecar.py:139-141).\n- YAGNI satisfied: each field (det_ms/llm_ms/total_ms/llm_calls/claim_path) maps directly to the db7b AC5 contract being restored — current done-definition, not hypothetical.\n- Not a premature abstraction: `_attach_plan_review_metrics` is a single-purpose helper, not a forced generalization.\n- The retired `run_review` was the prior production producer (story B-RETIRE), not a designated experiment/POC, so reconstructing equivalent telemetry on the surviving workflow path is the intended lifecycle — not a rebuild-vs-extend NIH concern."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782545736223703001,"uuid":"92a589a6-256d-4daf-85da-7f713f2b86de"}